    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An Election Equation: Nader and the X Factor</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gregory Low letter blames power of Ralph Nader's candidacy to exclusion of third parties from presidential debates (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mr. Nader's Electoral Mischief'' (editorial, Oct. 26):</p>
        <p>More power to Ralph Nader. By their exclusion of third parties from the presidential debates, the two main parties have effectively removed the ''democratic'' from our democratic process, but the media, yourself included, allow us the illusion that we still have it. Wonderful.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mr. Nader's Electoral Mischief'' (editorial, Oct. 26):</p>
        <p>More power to Ralph Nader. By their exclusion of third parties from the presidential debates, the two main parties have effectively removed the ''democratic'' from our democratic process, but the media, yourself included, allow us the illusion that we still have it. Wonderful.</p>
        <p>If third parties were actively in the debate process, it might be Mr. Nader who would be saying a vote for Al Gore is a vote for George W. Bush.</p>
        <p>GREGORY LOW  Buckfield, Me., Oct. 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
